<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-125] empty host header with ip address</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-125</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>file: HttpMethodBase.java method: addHostRequestHeader&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
HttpClient writes an empty Host header if the host is referred using IP address.&lt;br/&gt;
HTTP 1.1 RFC is not too clear what should be used in this case. However, other&lt;br/&gt;
HTTP 1.1 implementations (e.g. Java 1.4.0) uses IP address instead of dns name&lt;br/&gt;
in the header.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Furthermore, some HTTP server implementations (e.g. Jetty) will return &amp;quot;400 bad&lt;br/&gt;
request&amp;quot; if it encounters an empty Host header. That may be a bug in Jetty, but&lt;br/&gt;
it might be a good idea to use IP address in Host header to increase compability.</description>
                <environment>Operating System: All&lt;br/&gt;
